This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve the details of a sale. The response will include a status code of 200, along with a message and an array of sales. Each sale in the array contains information about the product, quantity, sale price, employee involved, total price, and buyer name. The product details include code, fiscal status, category, name, quantity, cost price, sale price, purchase month, purchase year, supplier, and product ID. The category includes name, fiscal code, and ID, while the supplier details consist of name, description, and ID. The employee details include name, job, and ID. Each sale also has its own unique ID.

**Response Example**

``` json
{
    "message": "All sales found.",
    "sales": [
        {
            "product": {
                "code": "0.10215313967638062",
                "isFiscal": true,
                "category": {
                    "name": "Brinco",
                    "fiscalCode": "12,123,12",
                    "id": "654bef730041c648ff868755"
                },
                "name": "Brinco de Ouro",
                "quantity": 1,
                "costPrice": 200,
                "salePrice": 260,
                "purchaseMonth": "Janeiro",
                "purchaseYear": 2023,
                "supplier": {
                    "name": "Alice",
                    "description": "Alice de Belo Horizonte",
                    "id": "654bef860041c648ff86875d"
                },
                "id": "654bef980041c648ff868766"
            },
            "quantity": 1,
            "salePrice": 260,
            "employee": {
                "name": "Vinícius",
                "job": "Vendedor",
                "id": "6552a63c57d36820f305810f"
            },
            "totalPrice": 260,
            "buyerName": "Ana Paula",
            "id": "6552a66057d36820f305811a"
        }
    ]
}

 ```

This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve the total profit for each employee. The request does not require a request body.

The response will have a status code of 200, and it will include a message and an array of results. Each result will contain the employee's name and their total sale amount.

**Response Example**

``` json
{
    "message": "All data found",
    "result": [
        {
            "employee": "Diego",
            "totalSale": 2070
        },
        {
            "employee": "Lucas",
            "totalSale": 780
        },
        {
            "employee": "Alice",
            "totalSale": 300
        }
    ]
}

 ```

This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve the percentage sales for each category. The request does not contain a request body.

### Response

- Status: 200
- The response will include a message and an array of objects containing the category and its corresponding percentage of sales.


**Response Example**

``` json
{
    "message": "All data found",
    "result": [
        {
            "category": "Calça",
            "percentage": 0.6206896551724138
        },
        {
            "category": "Brinco",
            "percentage": 0.20689655172413793
        },
        {
            "category": "Sapato",
            "percentage": 0.1724137931034483
        }
    ]
}

 ```
